# ── Godot editor / import cache ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/.godot/
/.import/
export.cfg
export_presets.cfg

# ── Local user state ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
look_settings.json
/out/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MetaHuman-derived ASSETS — DO NOT DISTRIBUTE.
#
# This is a "bring your own MetaHuman" tool. Epic's MetaHuman license (as of
# June 2025) permits using MetaHumans in other engines, but we deliberately do
# NOT redistribute the raw character meshes/textures/grooms in this public repo.
# Each user supplies their own licensed MetaHuman export.
#
# Drop your own export at godot_project/character.glb (+ its textures) and the
# tool uses it; otherwise it shows a neutral placeholder.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
character.glb
*.glb
*.fbx
*.png
*.exr
*.tga
*.hdr
# Godot import sidecars for the above (leak asset names + point at the cache)
*.png.import
*.glb.import
*.fbx.import
*.exr.import
*.tga.import
*.hdr.import

# ── Dev cruft / local backups — not for publication ──────────────────────────
*.bak
*.out
/_tex_backup_mhtest/
/textures_split/
# Unused vendored MatMADNESS copies (incl. an embedded git repo). The shaders we
# actually use are the local scenes/*.gdshader, which carry the MatMADNESS MIT
# header; full attribution is in LICENSE. Nothing references res://addons/.
/addons/

# Keep nothing MetaHuman-derived. (Project icon is icon.svg — SVG, not ignored.)
# NOTE: the broad *.png rule also excludes the MIT MatMADNESS addon's own bundled
# textures under addons/. Our scenes use the local scenes/*.gdshader copies, so
# this doesn't break them — but if we ever ship the addon standalone, carve those
# back in. A full "what to actually publish" repo curation is a follow-up.
